15/01/2006
VIENNA, Austria -- The new OSCE Chairman-in-Office, Belgian Foreign Minister Karel De Gucht, has cited Kosovo as a top priority and announced his plans to visit the region in February.
"This will be a critical year for Kosovo.
Negotiations on the future status have started.
The OSCE, with its massive presence on the ground, is bound to play a major role when UNMIK winds down its mission," De Gucht said during an address to the OSCE Permanent Council in Vienna Thursday (12 January).
In other news, the Contact Group for Kosovo is expected to convene in Vienna on Monday.
The Group members will discuss the current situation in Kosovo and further steps in the process of settlement of the province's final status.
(RTS - 15/01/06;
OSCE Web site - 12/01/06)
